Sentencas: The performance of YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+delta(YBSCCO)-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9(SDC) composite cathode for SOFC is investigated in this paper.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of the YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ cathode material by Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 incorporation for solid oxide fuel cells application

Sentencas: YBSCCO and SDC oxides are synthesized by the sol-gel method.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of the YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ cathode material by Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 incorporation for solid oxide fuel cells application

Sentencas: The XRD result reveals that no obvious chemical reaction occurs after sintering the mixture of the YBSCCO and SDC at 850 degrees C for 20 h. The thermal expansion behavior shows that the YBSCCO-xSDC composite cathode has the suitable TEC values (13.3-11.2 x 10(-6) K-1) for the common electrolyte.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of the YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ cathode material by Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 incorporation for solid oxide fuel cells application

Sentencas: In different proportions of the composite cathode, YBSCCO-30SDC shows the lowest polarization resistance values, which are only about 0.022 omega cm(2)at 850 degrees C and 0.034 omega cm(2)at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of the YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ cathode material by Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 incorporation for solid oxide fuel cells application

Sentencas: The electrolyte-supported single cell using YBSCCO-30SDC cathode is fabricated, and the peak power densities values are 567 and 432 mW cm(-2)at 850 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of the YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ cathode material by Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 incorporation for solid oxide fuel cells application
